  "original_title": "\u0db8\u0db1\u0dca\u0dad\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0dc0\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dca\u0d9c\u0dda \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dc1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0db4\u0db1\u0dc4\u0d9a\u0da7 \u0dc4\u0dd9\u0da7 \u0db8\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0db6\u0dba\u0dda\u0daf\u0dd3 \u0db4\u0dd2\u0dc5\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dd4",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Answers to 50 MPs' questions in the meeting tomorrow",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "MPs will have the opportunity to get answers to 50 delayed questions that have not been asked for a long time today (4) Monday in the meeting.",
        "Taking into account the requests of many people, the Committee on Parliamentary Affairs recently decided to allocate a separate day for the questions of the MPs.",
        "Thus, the entire time from 10:00 am to 03:30 pm will be allocated in the Parliament today (4) for the questions of the MPs.",
        "Meanwhile, orders under the Foreign Exchange Act No. 12 of 2017, orders published in Gazette Nos. 2270/59 and 2280/32 under the Export Development Act No. 40 of 1979, Resolutions regarding import duties under the Customs Ordinance Act and No. 7 of 2020 Parliamentary Secretary General Dhammika Dasanayake said that the proposal under Section 8 of the Appropriation Act will be approved tomorrow (5) after debate.",
        "Furthermore, 6 provisions under the Special Trade Goods Tax Act No. 48 of 2007 and the regulations published in the Gazette No. 2282/21 and 2282/22 under the Import and Export Control Act No. 1 of 1969 are to be adopted after debate on that day.",
        "Then, at the time of adjournment of the House, time is reserved for questions from 4.30 pm to 4.50 pm. According to the proposal submitted by the government, the debate has been decided to be held from 4.50 pm to 5.30 pm when the assembly is adjourned."
      ],
